.el .ds Aq '
.TH chat 1  "chat " 
.SH NAME
chat \- Start an interactive chat session with the agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBchat\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Start an interactive chat session with the agent.
.PP
The agent has access to tools: bash, file read/write/edit, and web search. It loads context from ~/.config/regin/context.md and .repo/regin/context.md (if present in cwd), plus all saved memories.
.PP
In\-session commands: /new       Start a new conversation /history   List previous conversations /quit      Exit the session
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH EXTRA
The agent runs commands and edits files on your behalf.
Context files and memories are loaded automatically as system prompts.
